column2: To participate, please give your consent and complete the questionnaire. All data is anonymized. No personal information will be shared. By participating in the study you will be assisting in understanding how people interpret social interactions and behaviors. As a baseline, there are no risks to participating in this study. The survey should take 10 minutes to complete. Personal contact is: dressagenerd@yahoo.com. By writing something below you are acknowledging that your consent is voluntary and you have the right to pull back consent at any time.
column4: Emily is sitting on a park bench watching children play on the playground. She does not have any children of her own but she enjoys watching them play. A child falls to the ground and no one comes to help, so she walks over to help the child off of the ground. How appropriate was Emily's behavior?
column5: Serena is a manager at a fortune 500 company.  In a meeting Serena's colleague interrupts her as she is presenting. To reassume control Serena asserts herself by speaking over her colleague and continues with her presentation. How appropriate was Serena's behavior?
column6: Angela is at a party where a man inappropriately touches her backside. Angela considers this deeply disrespectful and shoves the man against the wall and tells him he is not to lay a hand on her. How appropriate was Angela's behavior?
column7: Rachel is sitting on a park bench next to her husband. Her husband is quiet for a while before telling her he no longer wishes to be married. That he no longer loves her and has purchased a separate apartment, which he will be moving into later that week. Shock overwhelms Rachel and she begins to cry and wails loudly enough to draw the attention of people around them. How appropriate was Rachel's reaction?
column8: Lorelai is struggling with a difficult research subject at her university, despite her hard work her efforts never seem to be enough. She questions her ability as a scientist and consults a close friend. The friend says, maybe you're just not cut out for this field and should consider trying something new. Lorelai is angered by this suggestion and tells her friend, struggling doesn't mean quitting. Struggling doesn't mean I'm incapable. Just because you're a quitter who is threatened by anyone who tries, doesn't mean I should quit too. How appropriate was Lorelai's reaction?
column9: Holly is in an office building. She sees a male coworker trip and drop all of his paperwork, folders and notebooks onto the floor. The papers are scattered across the floor and it is clear Holly's coworker would appreciate help but Holly decides it isn't her problem and goes on with her day. How appropriate was Holly's behavior?
